True values: $a = 0.5$, $b = 0.8$, $c = 0.3$, indirect $= 0.4$, total $= 0.7$.

### Specify and fit the model

The spec uses **labeled coefficients** (`a*X`, `b*M`, `c*X`) and **defined parameters** (`:=`) for derived quantities.
Labels attach names to regression weights; defined parameters compute arbitrary posterior-draw-level expressions from those labels.

::: {#2f4eb2a2 .cell execution_count=2}
``` {.python .cell-code}
spec = """
M ~ a*X
Y ~ b*M + c*X
indirect := a*b
total := c + a*b
"""

model = pathmc.model(spec, data=df)
```
:::


::: {#74d9988b .cell execution_count=3}
``` {.python .cell-code}
model.graph()
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=3}
![](mediation_files/figure-html/cell-4-output-1.svg){}
:::
:::


::: {#169b9297 .cell execution_count=4}
``` {.python .cell-code}
model.equations()
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display .cell-output-markdown execution_count=4}
$$
\begin{aligned}
\beta_{M} &\sim \text{Normal}(mu=0,\, sigma=10) \\
\sigma_{M} &\sim \text{HalfNormal}(sigma=1) \\
\beta_{Y} &\sim \text{Normal}(mu=0,\, sigma=10) \\
\sigma_{Y} &\sim \text{HalfNormal}(sigma=1)
\\[6pt]
\mu_{M} &= \beta_{0,\,M} + a \cdot \mathrm{X} \\
\mathrm{M} &\sim \text{Normal}(\mu_{M},\, \sigma_{M}) \\
\mu_{Y} &= \beta_{0,\,Y} + b \cdot \mathrm{M} + c \cdot \mathrm{X} \\
\mathrm{Y} &\sim \text{Normal}(\mu_{Y},\, \sigma_{Y}) \\
indirect &\equiv a \cdot b \\
total &\equiv c + a \cdot b
\end{aligned}
$$
:::
:::


::: {#8bfd3c71 .cell execution_count=5}
``` {.python .cell-code}
model.fit(draws=500, tune=500, chains=4, random_seed=42)
```

